    "body": "Interesting. A quick glance at geth -- I don't think we'd 'detect' such misbehaving encodings: \r\n```golang\r\n\tcase msg.Code == discMsg:\r\n\t\t// This is the last message. We don't need to discard or\r\n\t\t// check errors because, the connection will be closed after it.\r\n\t\tvar m struct{ R DiscReason }\r\n\t\trlp.Decode(msg.Payload, &m)\r\n\t\treturn m.R\r\n```\r\nWe'd simply ignore the error returned during decoding, and the reason would be `0`: `disconnect requested`. ",
